  "body": "On `next`, specifying a truffle config to use a caret in compilers.solc.version (like so):\r\n\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  compilers: {\r\n    solc: {\r\n      version: \"^0.5.0\", <----\r\n      settings: {\r\n        optimizer: {\r\n          enabled: false,\r\n          runs: 200\r\n        },\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill result in this error when calling `truffle compile` in a valid truffle directory:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: Could not find a compiler version matching ^0.5.0. Please ensure you are specifying a valid version, constraint or build in the truffle config. Run `truffle compile --list` to see available versions.\r\n    at CompilerSupplier.errors (/Users/cruzmolina/Code/truffle-projects/truffle/packages/truffle-compile/compilerSupplier.js:533:10)\r\n    at CompilerSupplier.getByUrl (/Users/cruzmolina/Code/truffle-projects/truffle/packages/truffle-compile/compilerSupplier.js:260:25)\r\n    at process.internalTickCallback (internal/process/next_tick.js:77:7)\r\n```",
